Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.96,0:00:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're part of that emergence.\NWe're the leading edge of homospiritus,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.00,0:00:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of\Na new
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.80,0:00:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,being\Nalmost spiritous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.24,0:00:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When the the evolution of consciousness\Ncrossed over 200, it signal the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.92,0:00:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,emergence of a new\Nlevel of life, a new potentiality of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.52,0:00:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,life\Nbecause it's a more powerful level of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NThen it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.92,0:00:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is of assistance to spiritual\Nprogression
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.84,0:00:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to my\Nguess is that spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.28,0:01:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness will progress more rapidly and\Nreach more people than it has in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.55,0:01:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,past. Profoundly affect more aspects of\Nsociety.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.72,0:01:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that within the last few months.\NWe see that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.24,0:01:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that\Nback when the consciousness level was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,below 190\Nwhen I grew up winning gain wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.79,0:01:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,prestige fame\Nhaving a cat Cadillac titles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.20,0:01:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,degrees\Nall the gains the worldly gains
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.96,0:01:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the corner office with two windows\NHaving three secretaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.11,0:01:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the right address\Nthat which was sought was gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Its downside was victory over one's\Nenemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.00,0:02:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill the Japs, kill the Nazis, kill\Nsomebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.24,0:02:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so kill somebody. Kill your enemies.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.84,0:02:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the criteria of success were you went to\Nwar, you killed your enemies, then you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.08,0:02:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,came home, got a degree straight A, got\Ndoctorates, made millions of dollars,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.68,0:02:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,lived in the best place.\NThat was the signal of success
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a millionaire.\NThere's a TV program.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.95,0:02:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be a millionaire.\NI mean, it sounds stupid, you know, so
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.00,0:02:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,juvenile, but at the time it was very\Nexciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.36,0:02:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when the $64 question was\Nexciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.87,0:02:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,$64 to get you from here to New York and\Nback. You know, now it wouldn't get you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.64,0:02:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to Cottonwood.\NWouldn't get you in out of Walmart,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:03:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that's for sure.\NI'll say, "By God, this time I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.04,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to Walmart and I'm just going to buy\Nthose screens. That's all I'm buying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those grills. $163 it cost me.\N$16 grills."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nnow we see all that's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.36,0:03:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, winning over our enemies is even\Nquestioned. We're going through
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,soularching.\NWe got some really heavy duty enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.84,0:03:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,out there and the whole country is\Nexamining their conscience. Is it okay
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.68,0:03:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to go after your enemies or not? Defend\Nyourself against them or stand up to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.36,0:03:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,them or put them out of business before\Nthey do you in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the new\Nyard stick of success, the new yard
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.28,0:03:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,stick in society is integrity.\NIntegrity is where it's at right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.79,0:04:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of lack of integrity, we see the\Nmulti-millionaire corporations collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Enron and Altel and Mil work and Pom\NGump and all those cray
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.28,0:04:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,ticky names. Anyway,\Nthey sought the old paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.75,0:04:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Success at any cost. Man, what's wrong\Nwith that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.80,0:04:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,back at the time of the robber barons. I\Nmean that what was wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.88,0:04:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't anything immoral about\Nworking the workers to death and firing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.36,0:04:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,them before Christmas.\NYou big corporations always fired them
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the week before Christmas. And I say,\N"Good God, have they no sense at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't they have any public relations\Nperson? They have just injured their
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.04,0:04:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,corporation\Nfar more. or they spend millions on
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,advertising and then they find they\Nalways do all the big layoffs the week
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.68,0:04:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,before Christmas\Nin the public esteem they went from here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:05:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,down to here you know couldn't they wait\Ntill the week after Christmas
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.84,0:05:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,always the week before Christmas I don't\Nknow if you grew up in the 50s and 40s
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.28,0:05:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and 60s they all lay them off the week\Nbefore Christmas
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.72,0:05:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,now the new level\Nto which we're answerable now is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.28,0:05:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity\Nbecause Because of lack of integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.44,0:05:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the famous lady with her own magazine\Nand all multi-millionaire had resigned
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.16,0:05:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from the board of directors of the stock\Nmarket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.36,0:05:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Not because she was convicted of\Nanything, but because her integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.44,0:05:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity was now in question. That was\Nnever heard of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.56,0:05:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All of you who are older, did you ever\Nhear of anybody getting knocked off the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.68,0:05:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,border directly to some corporation for\Nlack of integrity? Never heard of it. He
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,got his job by being having lack of\Nintegrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.52,0:05:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If you didn't have lack of integrity,\Nyou're never going to be a salesman in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.72,0:05:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that company. I'll tell you,\Ntell him anything. Just get them to sign
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.80,0:06:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the D line and make sure the check gets\Ncertified. That's the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.40,0:06:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a salesman, you're supposed\Nto company the customer to the bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Roofing and siding.\NRoofing and siding. I saw roofing and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.24,0:06:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,siding. House to house. Lord, forgive\Nme. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.19,0:06:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.\NOh. All right. So we have a new paradigm
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.12,0:06:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of reality now. A very powerful\Nparadigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.19,0:06:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the networks\Nwhose own integrity is questionable at
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.31,0:06:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,times are touting integrity as the new\Nparadigm of reality, not success. Nobody
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,gives a crap about your success. Being a\Nmillionaire doesn't mean anything. All
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.56,0:07:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,kinds of poor folks became millionaires\Nduring the tech high-tech stock market
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.59,0:07:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,expansion.\NI had patients that could hardly afford
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.59,0:07:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a tank of gas to be truthful with you.\NBut they were millionaires.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.80,0:07:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day they check their stocks on the\Non their computer, you know. God, they
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.08,0:07:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,were worth $10 million. You know, by\Nnoon they're worth the $12 million. By 3
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.80,0:07:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the afternoon, they're worth $14\Nmillion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.72,0:07:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Except they lacked integrity. You see?\NSo now I want to be a millionaire. It
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.59,0:07:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds sort of stupid. Everybody got a\Nchance to shot to be a millionaire. If
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you didn't, your aunt did or your\Nneighbor did. I mean, being a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.47,0:07:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,millionaire doesn't mean anything.\NSuccess doesn't mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.56,0:07:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What holds up long term is integrity.\NAnd everybody knows that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:08:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the businesses we calibrated before we\Npublished power versus force as integras
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.56,0:08:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is now the biggest corporation in the\Nworld the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.87,0:08:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If that doesn't prove an integrity pace,\Nthen what does?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.31,0:08:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So business now, some members of this\Ngroup here are working
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.03,0:08:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry that message into business that\Nyour bottom line nowadays doesn't depend
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.72,0:08:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on how many you sell. That'll give you a\Nlittle pop on your stock, but it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.00,0:08:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,going to carry it through. I wouldn't\Nput that in your 401k, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.08,0:08:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What you better put in your 401k is\Nintegrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.24,0:08:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So that 30 years from now when you need\Nthat 401k, it hasn't gone down the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.15,0:08:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,drain. And the only thing I know that'll\Nkeep it from going down the drain is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.56,0:08:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity.\NWhy? Because integrity itself, just like
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.51,0:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the broken window drags that which is\Nnegative to it, that which is positive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,pulls that which is positive to it.\NI'd like to be a greeter in Walmarts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.83,0:09:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd really like that as a job. I mean, I\Njust love you. You imagine just hug
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,people all day and love them.\NWhat can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the underwear?\NWhere's the hats?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.92,0:09:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what a fun job. You know, that\Nwas as fun as being a cab driver. I like
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.39,0:09:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,being a cab driver. Oh, that was fun.\NBe a cab driver. You chatter and you're
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.60,0:09:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,friends with all the people. By the time\Nthey leave the cab, you're less best
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.56,0:09:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,buddies. You know what I mean? He wants\Nyour phone number. He wants you to come
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.24,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to his sister's birthday party next\Nweek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.00,0:09:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The chance to just love lots of people\Nunconditionally is just, you know, a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,really great opportunity.\NIt's probably why I gave up being a vger
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.95,0:10:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in a cathedral.\NThe life of the solitary monk has its
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.36,0:10:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,virtue.\NEverybody needs a life as a solitary
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.16,0:10:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,monk. And um it's a great life\Nbecause through that absolute
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.24,0:10:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,aloneeness, the simplicity to just have\Na candle and a stick and a book in a in
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.27,0:10:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a chair, you really don't need anything\Nmore. You really do not need anything
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.32,0:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,more. And when I came out to Sedona,\Nthat's the way we lived for quite a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,while. With a box, a candle with an\Napple and a cot from a dinosaur.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.00,0:10:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fantastic.\NThen life got worse. I started to own
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.56,0:10:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,things.\NGot worse and worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.24,0:10:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh man.\NBecome a captive of your own
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.80,0:11:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,possessions.\Nto become their slave, their servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.72,0:11:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\NSo we find God through simplicity,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.88,0:11:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,through renunciation.\NThe renunciation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.12,0:11:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can be physical, social.\NThe renunciation
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.20,0:11:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is internal to renounce\Nto be willing to surrender out of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.00,0:11:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,devotion to God the satisfaction and the\Ngratification one gets out of one's
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.83,0:11:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mental gerations\Nto juice revenge to juice resentment to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.72,0:11:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,juice self-pity\Nat the same time not make them wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.72,0:11:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we let go these positions. We\Nlet go our attachment to them, but not
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.12,0:12:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out of guilt and making them wrong.\NI like to complain and grumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.60,0:12:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I say to her, "Honey,\Nif we didn't have each other to complain
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and grumble to, who the heck would we\Ntalk to?" Now, one of our forms of love
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is we both listen to each other's\Ngrumbles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.24,0:12:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The air conditioning on my car doesn't\Nwork now, and I can't drive it to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Phoenix now because it doesn't work.\NShe says, "Oh, that's awful. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.76,0:12:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,take my car.\NThe close neighbor who works with us,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.12,0:12:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Lou, has has computer trouble with his\Ncar. I hope he complains to somebody. He
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,hasn't complained to me, but if I were\Nhim, I'd complain about it. I paid good
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,money for the car. The computer doesn't\Nwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.20,0:12:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to have somebody to grumble to\Nand be human with. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:13:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, you take your own self with a\Ndash of salt. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.04,0:13:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take yourself too seriously.\NYou can indulge yourself, but not take
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.88,0:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it too seriously. You can have a\Ntantrum. You can throw yourself on the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,floor. It's good. It's good. It's fun.\NYou just throw yourself on the floor and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.48,0:13:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,just scream with anger and hit the\Nfloor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.39,0:13:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then everybody is a six-month-old.\NSo you don't make it wrong. You see what
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.12,0:13:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean? Within all of us is the is the\Nvindictive judge. You're going to be put
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,away and suffer for this young man\Nand never see the light of day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.04,0:13:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You see? Yes, sir.\NSo to transcend something, you have to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.04,0:13:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to accept it. To accept it, you\Nhave to get off right and wrong about
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.56,0:14:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it. It just is that way. There's ugly\Nlittle creatures in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.24,0:14:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Their mothers love them, but nobody else\Ndoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all right for them to be there\Nbecause consciousness evolves and it and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.19,0:14:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it expresses itself in form\Nthroughout its evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.56,0:14:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we look around the manifest world,\Nwe see all these levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.44,0:14:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\Nsome lower than what we even have on the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.00,0:14:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,chart.\NPoisonous little things that live at the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom of the sea.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's like all these levels of\Nconsciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.07,0:14:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,express themsel in form\Nand each one then is like a stepping
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.88,0:14:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,stone.\NSo we look within ourself and we see all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that's possible within the field of\Nconsciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.32,0:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All the positives and all the things we\Ncall negatives and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And we get off a positionality about our\Nown positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.24,0:15:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's natural to have positionalities.\NRight and wrong, good and evil,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.95,0:15:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,love and hate. Um they're not opposites.\NThey're positionalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.48,0:15:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all positionalities along the\Nsame line. They're not opposites. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.39,0:15:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,have to always confirm that\Nbecause to undo the ego, you have to let
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.36,0:15:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,go positionalities. And positionalities\Nare set set up by the dualistic
