Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.96,0:32:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's shocking to yourself even when you\Nsuddenly make a giant leap in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.03,0:32:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness and suddenly you're almost\Nstunned by the beauty and the silence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.24,0:32:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the presence of God as\Nlove
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.51,0:33:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,with an intensity beyond which one could\Neven imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.15,0:33:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The presence of God as infinite love is\Noverwhelming
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.88,0:33:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and it does take you out the world.\NAnybody
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.27,0:33:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who's seriously committed to spiritual\Nwork, I always tell them, be sure your
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.03,0:33:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,relatives know what you're up to or your\Nfriend or somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.67,0:33:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Because at any moment, one can go into a\Nstate that cannot be conveyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.36,0:33:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,described.\NOne becomes speechless.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.84,0:33:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Motion is almost impossible.\NIn higher states, you become weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.67,0:33:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is slowed down.\Nyou forget about eating, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.48,0:33:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,forget about all physical things.\NSo, you need somebody to know that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.88,0:33:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a spiritually committed person.\NAnd if you go into a silent state of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.51,0:33:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,bliss,\Nhe doesn't need shock treatment, doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.72,0:34:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,need a shot of thorazine.\NYou can suggest eating this with soup,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.12,0:34:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may not get much of an answer to\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.87,0:34:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual work is very serious work. It\Ncan bring about profound changes both
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.07,0:34:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,physically and\Nwithin one's sense of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.52,0:34:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of self.\NIt can change profoundly and in an
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.20,0:34:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,instant with no forewarning.\NMore usually one begins to feel joy more
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.72,0:34:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,often. Begin to notice the beauty of\Nthings that you didn't notice before.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.67,0:34:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certain sort of warnings\Ncoming up in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.91,0:34:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice how beautiful everyone is.\NYou tend to fall in love with
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.48,0:34:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.\NThere's that falling in love phase where
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.48,0:35:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you fall in love with all of life and\Neverything in it and everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.44,0:35:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's sort of a warning\Nto get your affairs in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.32,0:35:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Get your affairs in order\Nbecause one is like led to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.00,0:35:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that which you need to be led to. And\Nthen the willingness to surrender even
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.92,0:35:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that to God,\Neven ecstasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.76,0:35:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual ecstasy beyond description\Ncomes up to be surrendered
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.24,0:35:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee, oh God.\NOne time I was dancing in front of the
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.76,0:36:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,altar\Nat midnight
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.44,0:36:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the chapel over here.\NChapel of the Holy Cross. They didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.52,0:36:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,used to lock it.\NIt was open all night and the candles
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.40,0:36:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,burned all night and the music was on\Nall night
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.96,0:36:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the visitors had left and at\N12:00 or 1 in the morning you could go
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.20,0:36:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there\Nand meditate all alone in this chapel
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.96,0:36:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with the candle and the music and the\Nbeauty and you would just go into an
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.11,0:36:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ecstatic state beyond description.\NNow they lock it up, turn off the music
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.24,0:36:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and put the lights out. It's\Nhealth department or somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.40,0:36:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and such ecstatic states.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.59,0:37:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the ecstatic state\Nwas described by Rama Krishna. So after
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.48,0:37:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned that Rama Krishna went into\Nit, I quit worrying about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.04,0:37:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Such ecstatic state. So somebody has to\Ntell you that those states are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.24,0:37:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to be experienced. If\Nyou're being attracted by the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.16,0:37:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nof the evolution of human consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.83,0:37:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're going to be pulled through\Nthose states.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.72,0:37:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And when ecstasy beyond description,\Nthe willingness to surrender it even
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.35,0:37:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that to God,\Nwhen that's surrendered to God,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.28,0:37:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,then the most awesome of all,\Na piece of such profoundity, of such
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.68,0:37:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,extent, in such dimension,\Nand of such expression through its
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.35,0:37:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,quality and its exquisite presence takes\Nthe place of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.28,0:38:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,ecstasy\Nand that gets you beyond 599.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.04,0:38:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We got we told you how to get beyond the\N400s
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.40,0:38:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,now the 500s.\NThis you see the rean reverence love
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.35,0:38:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness\Nbrings one up to an exquisite joyfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.35,0:38:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,within which there is a serenity.\NThe revelation of the presence of God
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.72,0:38:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and a transfiguration takes place within\Nthe person. You will never be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.35,0:38:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You will never be the same again. to\Nexperience the presence of God when it's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.59,0:38:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is not possible to go back.\NThen up here is is the states
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.96,0:38:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this is just joy but up here should be\Necstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.16,0:38:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of joy\Nthat moves on to an ecstasy that's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.44,0:39:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond description\Nbeyond comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.92,0:39:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That exquisite bliss, that ecstatic\Necstasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.52,0:39:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to surrender even that\Nto God brings
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.68,0:39:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,an infinite state\Nwhich is all prevailing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.20,0:39:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the absolute rel reality that\Nprevails
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.76,0:39:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and in due time\None can go back into the world and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.24,0:39:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,be alive to the world without it being\Ndisturbed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.56,0:39:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The state is always present.\NThen one witnesses
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.20,0:39:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what was the person the persona\Nreturns to interact with the world if
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.20,0:39:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that's one's karmic propensity.\NIf that's one's karmic propensity,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.83,0:40:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,one may or may not return to the world.\NMost do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.88,0:40:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Most once you hit that state of peace,\Nthat's it. One is finished with the
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.68,0:40:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,world\Nand there is no obligation to remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.56,0:40:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But for unknown\Nkarmic reasons,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.96,0:40:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,one may stay.\NIn that case, the persona
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.68,0:40:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is given permission to react to\Nreactivate within the world to
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.64,0:40:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,respond to the world in a way the world\Ncomprehends within their dimensions of
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.64,0:40:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reality\Nand learns to refunction in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.16,0:40:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time one has located spiritual\Nteachers that are aware of such
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.04,0:41:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions.\NAnd I think it's the duty of the teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.56,0:41:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,always to warn\Nnot warn to educate about what these
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.59,0:41:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,states are how they come about\Nto know that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.80,0:41:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's all right.\NIt's all right to feel bliss and ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.35,0:41:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's all right to\Nlet the body fall over.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.52,0:41:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If it ceases to breathe, then it's\Nimmaterial.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.48,0:41:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One is not obligated to breathe it\Nagain.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.56,0:41:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people rebreathe it when it stops\Nbreathing cuz out of a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.31,0:41:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,obligation.\NSo one at that point one releases that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.88,0:41:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of obligation and becomes\Ndetached. You're not obliged to the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.59,0:42:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,world or anyone in it. So that's one of\Nthe last attachments.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.11,0:42:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One lets go.\NOn the way of spiritual progression,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.40,0:42:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing as this is a class of people who\Nare destined for the ultimate or they
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.24,0:42:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be here, we already reaffirmed\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.07,0:42:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,along the way. those especially when you\Nget into the 500s,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.59,0:42:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you begin to pull up\Num that
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.11,0:42:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is opposed to spirituality which\Nis threatened by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.92,0:42:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And\None has to watch
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.83,0:42:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that benevolence and lovingness does not\Ntake the form of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.04,0:42:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,naivity.\Nan ignorance and fall back into a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.04,0:42:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,different ignorance\Nto be loving but at the same time guard
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.04,0:43:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the gates.\NThere's a certain phase in the 500s
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.04,0:43:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,where one becomes um\Num a target of that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.92,0:43:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integrous.\NThey see your vulnerability. There is a
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.11,0:43:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,certain phase in that level where you\Ncannot see anything with love. And
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.96,0:43:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,so\None has to still preserve integrity. So
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.11,0:43:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the safeguard then\Nin the 500s the levels of love is still
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.72,0:43:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,then\Nto recall integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.07,0:43:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is what they are presenting to you\Nintegrous
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.80,0:43:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,um because it can be cleverly conveyed\Nto sell what you know for a price
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.59,0:44:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. it comes up as a temptation.\NSo I've spoken in previous lectures
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.28,0:44:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,about\Nthe luciferic temptation of power over
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.20,0:44:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,others\Nuh money, power, fame
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.04,0:44:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and seduction in its various forms.\NCertain entities will see a person in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.20,0:44:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that blissful state of lovingness\Nas vulnerable. So
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.59,0:44:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,one's protection then is integrity.\NIt's not loving to allow others to be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.68,0:44:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,non-integorous with you.\NThat's confusing love with passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.88,0:44:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not of service to yourself or\Nothers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.48,0:44:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow that which is non-intigorous\Nto have an effect on your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.20,0:44:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have integrity then we have to let\Nexecutives go
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.83,0:45:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in and the name of the business because\Nfor the business to survive it has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.76,0:45:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the rock of integrity which\Nwill survive success.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.92,0:45:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Without integrity\Nyou cannot survive success.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.52,0:45:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, we've talked enough of\Nthis morning about
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.68,0:45:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the evolution of consciousness because\Nas it manifests as yourself, you
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.72,0:45:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,personalize it. You personalize it. But\Nwhat you're personalizing itself is not
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.31,0:45:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,personal. It's consciousness.\NAnd you are merely calling it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.56,0:45:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,me or myself.\NBut that's just what you're calling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.04,0:45:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you see that you're just calling\Nit that and that it's innately it's
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.07,0:45:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,neither this nor that nor is it here nor\Nthere. One realizes that what is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.44,0:46:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking as consciousness itself what is\Npresenting itself to your own awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.92,0:46:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is the divinity within expressing itself\Nas the joy of one's own existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.68,0:46:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,source of joy then is the awareness of\Nthe presence of God within
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.76,0:46:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as one's own existence.\NThank you Lord for the existence of all
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.59,0:46:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in this audience\Nand thank you for my existence and for
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.96,0:46:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,sharing it with you because we\Napparently are all destined for the same
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.68,0:46:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,place.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.04,0:47:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.80,0:47:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.76,0:47:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelu\NHallelu
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.44,0:47:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.92,0:47:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.07,0:47:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.16,0:48:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelujah.\NHalleluah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.48,0:48:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Halleluah.\NHallelu.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.56,0:48:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Halleluah.\NHalleluah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.56,0:48:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelu\NHalleluahalleluah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.88,0:48:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hallelu\NHallelujah.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.83,0:48:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> If you can't find God, all you have to\Ndo is turn this music on
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.96,0:49:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and do nothing else.\NYou hear the essence of the exquisite
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.55,0:49:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,presence expressing itself as beauty\Nand infinite compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.11,0:49:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to God is extremely radical at\Ntimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.96,0:49:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick up a prayer here, a hymn there,\Nattend a workshop here, read a book
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.80,0:49:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NI can't figure out I can't seem to make
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.44,0:49:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,any progress.\NOne finds that which is sympatical with
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.40,0:49:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,oneself and then persists with it with a\Ndogged
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.80,0:49:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,determination\Nand absolute commitment beyond all
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.35,0:49:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,commitments.\NIf you find it through this music,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.59,0:50:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you play this music round the clock\Nnow and forever more.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.92,0:50:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to eat. You don't have to\Ngo to the bathroom. Have to go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.55,0:50:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to answer the phone.\NThere comes a time when you decide to
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.07,0:50:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,make the run for it.\NIt can be a mantra. It can be a
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.76,0:50:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,meditation.\NIt can be meditating on a guru.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.52,0:50:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be something that you consider\Ndivine, sacred.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.20,0:50:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And you go with it\Nno matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.48,0:50:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what.\NAnd if you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.68,0:50:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't eat after a couple weeks and death\Nfaces you, so you die.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.40,0:51:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nthat's the least of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.92,0:51:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Dying is a snap. Is a college way out.\NHe's taken by everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.55,0:51:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, brother. Going to get to heaven by\Ndying? Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.07,0:51:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you you get there by a fixity, a\Nfocus and a determination.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.68,0:51:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an act of the spiritual will.\NIt is by an act of the spiritual will
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.59,0:51:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have already chosen your future\Nand that's why you're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.52,0:51:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a letter the other day. It says,\N"I've read the first six pages of the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.59,0:52:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,preface and I have to talk to you right\Naway.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.64,0:52:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a fact? That is a fact that I've\Nread the first six pages and I must talk
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.59,0:52:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to you right away.\NI mean that uh it was it was adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.55,0:52:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know\Nwe get delued delused with uh all the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.07,0:52:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,forms of communication existent\Nnowadays. The fax goes round the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.72,0:52:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The email never stops. The computer\Nnever stops. The telephone never stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.00,0:52:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The answering machine never stops. The\Nanswering service never stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.40,0:52:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not possible to answer it all and I\Nread everything and I sort of mentally
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.72,0:52:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,communicate an answer\Nbut it's not possible within the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.04,0:53:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,physical domain to handle it.\NFirst of all, I can't type
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.76,0:53:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nthe office has bought a computer and I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.04,0:53:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can't find the on switch.\NI'm I'm not lying. I'm not there is no
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.24,0:53:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,on or off switch. So\Nbecause I couldn't get beyond that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.80,0:53:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,point, I gave it up. And I mean if you\Ncan't even find the onoff switch, do
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.28,0:53:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,stock, you know, it's not for you. You\Nknow, it's not in your dimension
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.04,0:53:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow.\NI just want to apologize to all the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.44,0:53:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,people who sent such beautiful\Ncommunications and I cannot answer them
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.04,0:53:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,all. We try to answer questions here.\NThe answers to most of the questions
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.92,0:53:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that people send are already within the\Nwritten material or the visuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.40,0:53:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh I try to include everything that\Ncould possibly come up so that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.76,0:53:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,very often if a thing is not understood,\Nit hasn't been meditated on. That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.92,0:54:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't looked at it long enough.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.52,0:54:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,um most questions I feel like saying\Nwell look at it and call me back in 20
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.40,0:54:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,years.\NThose are the things I looked at.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.52,0:54:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like as you focus on a situation\Nmentally and ask for God's help to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.72,0:54:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,resolve it. Ask to see it differently.\NAsk for the miraculous. Pray to the Holy
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.96,0:54:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirit. and rattle the gates of heaven.\NWhen it's karmically allowed, you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.24,0:54:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly see it. You suddenly see the\Nanswer and it resolves itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.68,0:54:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nso
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.80,0:54:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work is different than\Nintellectual work. Intellectual work is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.07,0:54:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,asking a specific and then getting a\Nspecific answer and now you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.00,0:54:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,satisfied\Nwhich is too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.72,0:55:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The actual answer comes from\Nreflecting on a thing. So we talked
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.92,0:55:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,during these lectures about the style of\Na spiritually uh committed person
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.64,0:55:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes more and more contemplative\Nso that all that arises one
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.28,0:55:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,more or less contemplates\Nand in that way eventually bypass
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.55,0:55:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the polarities.\NIsn't peace good? And isn't war awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.88,0:55:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No. War is terrific.\NAnd peace is terrific. And frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.68,0:55:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they're actually the same. Except to the\Nobserver, they look like opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.00,0:55:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, the country is involved in\Nthe situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.24,0:55:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Should they should we be pacifist or\Nactivist?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.79,0:56:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we be reactive or proactive?\NThat's where it really comes down to.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.72,0:56:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are old enough remember World\NWar II and when and what went on that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.68,0:56:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,time. So those who have not learned from\Nhistory are condemned to repeat it. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.48,0:56:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember the prime minister of England\Ntaking a pacifist position with Adolf
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.11,0:56:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler and says, "Oh, he's a he's an\Nokay guy. All we have to do is this,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.24,0:56:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that, and the other." Right? So, you\Ncannot confuse passivity with peace
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.52,0:56:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,because very often passivity brings war.\NI lived through the era in which
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.24,0:56:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,passivity brought the death of 70\Nmillion people
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.79,0:56:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> after World War II, you know, after the\Nworld in 1929,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.28,0:57:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Secretary of State, the new Secretary of\NState was Stimson, I believe. Simpson.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.83,0:57:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We had an intelligence service of course\Nduring World War I
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.07,0:57:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it continued after World War I.\Nand his first day in office as Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.07,0:57:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of State, the intelligence service\Npresented its report for the day
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.55,0:57:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Secretary of State who said,\Nquote, "Gentlemen, do not read other
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.16,0:57:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,gentlemen's mail."\NThat cost us another 70 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.44,0:57:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,dead. Cost us Pearl Harbor.\NI want to clarify that pacifism is not
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.11,0:57:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the same as taking the action that takes\Nyou to peace because peace
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.00,0:57:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,takes integrity. Integrity does not\Nallow itself to play ball with non-
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.28,0:58:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity. Right?\NTruth is often
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.44,0:58:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to stand one's ground and\Nsay no further, no more. Right? Somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.16,0:58:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,asked me that question during the\Nintermission.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.96,0:58:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the integra's stance?\NThe integra stance is not to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.07,0:58:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,allow your monastery to be ravaged by\Nwolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.16,0:58:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to protect your monastery.\NTo transcend the opposites then is to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.35,0:58:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,stop seeing one thing as\None thing and the other thing is its
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.68,0:58:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite.\NOne has to be in a very high state to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.55,0:58:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see\Nlike death
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.72,0:59:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or makes no difference.\NDie by the droves, die singly
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.79,0:59:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because the evolution of consciousness\Ntakes us through these various forms
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.92,0:59:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're somersault with them and you\Ngo the way of the Dao or you break. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.35,0:59:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's time for war, you go with the\Nwar. When it's time for peace, you go
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.64,0:59:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for peace. So what should a person do\Nabout it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.04,0:59:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,One should hold an integrous\Ndesire for peace
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.79,0:59:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and pray\Nand then allow
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.92,0:59:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,divine will to express itself in the\Nkarmic expression of humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.52,0:59:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times do you have to die in war\Nbefore you see it's absurd? A lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.72,0:59:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,times apparently\Nover and over and over again people
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.79,1:00:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,choose it. Yes.\Nover and over again
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.88,1:00:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,until people learn that part of\Nspirituality is integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.72,1:00:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrity means\Nto stop playing victim. It's not
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.92,1:00:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous to allow your husband to beat\Nyou all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.07,1:00:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Not integrous to allow your children to\Nbe abused. It's not integrous to allow
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.52,1:00:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,people to steal from you.\NThe illusion that one has to transcend
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.76,1:00:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in politics is that other people are\Nlike you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.64,1:00:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I got news for you. Other people are not\Nlike you at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.04,1:00:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people think you're a stupid\Nidiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.35,1:01:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The presumption, you see, from\Nan educated
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.00,1:01:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nconsciousness level of 430
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.16,1:01:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is to presume that other people are like\Nus. They wouldn't do that. They'd bring
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.92,1:01:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,destruction on their own people.\NOf course they would. And of course they
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.76,1:01:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would bring destruction on their own\Npeople. We see it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.44,1:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The leaders of other countries are not\Nin the same level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.00,1:01:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Megalamomania\Ndoesn't care if their whole country gets
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.35,1:01:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wiped out. It's very hard for sane\Npeople to realize the degree of insanity
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.11,1:01:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of megalomania.\NHitler not only didn't care because all
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.83,1:01:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,his people got killed,\Nhe thought they deserved it. In fact,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.92,1:01:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what was left standing, he would have\Neliminated if the generals had followed
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.28,1:02:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,his orders to burn Berlin to the ground.\Nthe recent dictator out of the Balkans
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.04,1:02:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,who's on trial in the UN Court of\NAppeals or whatever it is
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.11,1:02:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the same way.\NMegalamania is the you might say
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.59,1:02:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the extreme opposite of what we would\Nimagine divinity would being be.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.72,1:02:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is comes from the lower\Nastral
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.07,1:02:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,hates humans,\Nhates humanity.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.55,1:02:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is dominated by the lashal.\NWe have permission to ask resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.11,1:02:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hates humanity.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.83,1:02:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hates humanity. So you're going to put\Nyour trust
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.35,1:03:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in a dictator of another country that\Nhates humanity
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.92,1:03:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't hate you. It hates its own\Npeople.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.24,1:03:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The megalomaniac is not satisfied until\Nyou are wiped out and also his country.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.35,1:03:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants all of mankind destroyed.\NYou remember there was an era there
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.35,1:03:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,during the communist era when they were\Nplanning the mega bomb that if they lost
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.83,1:03:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the war would eliminate all of human\Nlife.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.35,1:03:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore\Nto be spiritual doesn't mean to be
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.16,1:03:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,foolish or blind to denial\Nand sacrifice needlessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.31,1:03:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,However, everything that mankind goes\Nthrough serves an ultimate lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.68,1:04:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we go through the same lesson over\Nand over until we get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.96,1:04:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't hand the keys to the car to a\Ndrinking alcoholic who is also psychotic
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.79,1:04:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and off his meds.\NBecause you're spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.16,1:04:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No folks, it won't happen that way.\NDoesn't. So, one of we the lesson those
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.88,1:04:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,are one of the lessons we learn along\Nthe spiritual pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.28,1:04:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is that naivity\Nis different than ign ignorance and
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.79,1:04:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that's different from innocence\Nand they are all different than denial.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.92,1:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What passes as spirituality is often\Ndenial.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.44,1:04:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a posturing ignorance\Nin assumed innocence
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.76,1:05:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which innocence itself does not need to\Nassume.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.55,1:05:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like humility does not have to\Nassume the position of pseudo humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.64,1:05:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The goody goody side of spirituality is\Navailable everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.52,1:05:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The goody goody side of spirituality\Nhas a big trap to it. Otherwise,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.44,1:05:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody would be enlightened.\NIt was easy to skyrocket to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.03,1:05:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody be there. We'd all be off this\Nplanet. Turn it back to the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.96,1:05:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They knew what to do with it.\NKill each other without being pious
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.64,1:05:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about it.\NThey were honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.59,1:05:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You look good. I'm going to eat you. I'm\Ngoing to kill you. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.35,1:05:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, no pretense that uh you know,\Nhe's just an innocent good fellow. And
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.44,1:05:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if we all pray for him, Tyrannosaurus\NRex will become like the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.31,1:06:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tyrannosaurus Rex will not become like\Nthe rest of us because he's run by
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.92,1:06:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,energies from a different domain.\NAll right? So
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.40,1:06:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,part of being spiritual is starting to\Nbecome integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.11,1:06:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It requires honesty and strength. Part\Nof the spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.79,1:06:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is the spiritual warrior who stands up\Nand defends the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.76,1:06:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Bin Laden is not going to become a good\Nguy and change his mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.76,1:06:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It ain't going to be\Nthe enemies of that which we have are
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.68,1:06:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,enemies because they hate that which we\Nhave and that which we are. Why does the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.88,1:06:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,lower astral hate,\Nhumanity?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.59,1:07:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because humanity has the chance to\Nreturn to God and they do not.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.64,1:07:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,those who have chosen\Nto deny God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.83,1:07:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. The hatred that would that emerges\Non this planet stems from the lower
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.83,1:07:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,astral resist.\NStems from the lower astral. It stems
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.64,1:07:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,from that which hates mankind. Resist.\NIt stems from that which would
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.28,1:07:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,like to destroy mankind.\NWould like to destroy God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.24,1:07:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and destroy all who seek God.\NAll right? So that should take care of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.68,1:07:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,naivity. You're not exactly walking\Namongst friends every moment of every
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.00,1:07:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,day.\NThat which hates God seeks to dominate
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.48,1:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and did dominate until the late late 18\N1980s.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.00,1:08:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness of mankind was below 200.\NThat which
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.03,1:08:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is hates God let's say\Nreally dominated the consciousness of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.11,1:08:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind the late 19 18 1980s\Nonly now are we crossing over where
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.75,1:08:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity has a chance\Nby turn by by before I turn over the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.08,1:08:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,cards in my checkbook to somebody I want\Nto see is credit rating
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.88,1:08:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that not spiritual? No, that's\Nspiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.04,1:08:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Pseudospiritual is, oh, I trust\Neverybody. I'm sure I can give anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.04,1:08:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,my checkbook and the keys to my car. And\NI know I can depend on him to return it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.60,1:08:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I got news for you. I had to go down\Nafter waiting a month to Cottonwood and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.88,1:08:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,get my car because it was still sitting\Nin the driveway cuz he was on a bender.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.79,1:09:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I never would have gotten my car back if\NI waited for the goodness of mankind to
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.44,1:09:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,blossom through this idiot.\NSo being spiritual doesn't mean being a
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.83,1:09:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,stupid willow.\NI say that because people that are pu,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.48,1:09:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, naive wallows get taken.\NThey get taken and not only not just
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.96,1:09:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,financially, they get taken spiritually.\NI got a new guru for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.83,1:09:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is dilletterious to the\Ntrue pathway
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.83,1:09:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,loves to snare the really committed\Nspiritual seeker. And what's his
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.56,1:09:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,downside? His downside is his naive.\NTherefore, as a teacher, it's my
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.23,1:10:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility\Nto get off the sweet willow path
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.32,1:10:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of flowers and hearts and hymns\Nand get with it that you got to be real
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.76,1:10:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to be spiritual.\NYou have to be able to accept the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.04,1:10:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,reality of how it is,\Nnot get into pretense.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.19,1:10:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of prayer is just pretenseful.\NYou can pray up a storm for being loud.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.80,1:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you weren't.\NHe doesn't want to go where you want to
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.04,1:10:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,go.\NIf he wanted to go where you would you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.67,1:10:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,want to go, he wouldn't be aligned with\Nthe lower astral forces.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.60,1:10:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand?\NHe wouldn't be he wouldn't be there. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.88,1:10:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all right.\NThere are things I don't know that I can
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.19,1:11:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,share everything I know. So, let's see.\NUm, we can answer this resist. Um, the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.19,1:11:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,fact is no.\NOkay. Those who have chosen
Dialogue: 0,1:11:07.52,1:11:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to deny God, to hate God, etc. are not\Nallowed to be delivered from hell. It
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.28,1:11:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,says\Nthey have chosen hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.92,1:11:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, there's some serious\Nspiritual errors that apparently
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.52,1:11:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some uh there's some spiritual\Nerrors you really want to avoid.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.08,1:11:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of the teacher, the guru, can\Nit advance your consciousness or undo
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.23,1:11:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,negative karma? Let's see.\NWe have permission to answer that. The
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.36,1:11:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,answer is yes.\NUm, I didn't know that the presence of
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.44,1:11:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the teacher.\NOh, I see. Being aligned. Let's see. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.19,1:12:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Being aligned with the it's the\Nalign with God, not the teacher. And
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.00,1:12:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,does the negative karma resist? Okay.\NYes. Because one's of one's devotion to
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.92,1:12:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God, one seeks a teacher. And it's\Nbecause of one's devotion to God that
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.84,1:12:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then the acting it out within the\Nphysical domain uh releases the negative
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.64,1:12:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,karma. That's true.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.76,1:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,much of the effect of the teacher is\Nvibrational. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.92,1:12:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Much of the effect of the teacher on\None's consciousness is strictly
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.44,1:12:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,vibrational. It's strictly the energy\Nenergy of the field resist. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.64,1:12:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,impersonal resist.\NIt's the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.23,1:12:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the power of divinity through the\Nvibrational energy the karmic field is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.44,1:13:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,expressing itself. I see in the oh I see\Nin the uh atmic body resist. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.04,1:13:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That the the energy field then of\Nthe teacher vibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.56,1:13:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own\Num aura picks it up. I remember
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.40,1:13:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,consciously picking it up from the\Nkarmapa. I saw the karmapa once many
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.12,1:13:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,years ago and I just got the vibrational\Nfield.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.84,1:13:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Had nothing to do with the karmappa. Had\Nto do with the vibrational field but I
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.52,1:13:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,caught it at that instant.\NYou were catching it before too
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.08,1:13:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when we were into the music together.\NDivinity is um available everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.71,1:13:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The recognition of it as beauty is\Na constant opportunity to reach God. One
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.32,1:13:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tunes in on beauty\Nlistens to beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.52,1:14:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of God is silent.\NThe sound of God is present at all
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.32,1:14:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,times.\NBehind the talkingness, behind the noise
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.84,1:14:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is a profound and infinite silence\Nin which is the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.80,1:14:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,so powerful\Nthat one has to resist it in order to
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.92,1:14:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,keep functioning in the world. And so\Nbeautiful music like that will take you
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.48,1:14:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,right out.\NYou have to sit down. it takes you right
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.92,1:14:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out of it because of the vibration of\Nthe beauty. Um so in the high 500s it
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.60,1:14:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes sometimes very difficult to\Nfunction
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.04,1:14:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because one is crying all the time and\Nevery little thing it's beauty just
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.36,1:14:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,knocks you out.\NYou have to stay away from kitties. They
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.96,1:14:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,blow you away.\NYou have to stay away from lovers.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.56,1:14:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,People that are in love. They're\Nterrible.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.19,1:14:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,One time I always missed the plane. I\Nwas sitting there waiting for the plane
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.32,1:15:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and this couple looked at each other and\Nwow, you could just see the load there.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.64,1:15:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost did not make the plane.\NI had to bring myself back.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.92,1:15:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Um,\Nhell.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.00,1:15:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\Nthere's different levels to hell. I
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.12,1:15:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know if I want to talk about hell\Ntoday, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.40,1:15:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nuh we can discuss this today.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.40,1:15:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There's various kinds of hell. There's\Ndifferent dimensions of hells or
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.08,1:15:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,different hells.\NThe hell that I was in, you still had a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.92,1:15:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,chance. Resist. Oh, thank you, Lord.\NI guess if you're even kind to one
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.96,1:15:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,simple little beetle, you get to\Nexperience hell but with the chance for
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.80,1:16:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,salvation\Nbecause I don't think there's much
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.71,1:16:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,deeper levels than I was at. Let's see.\NWe can discuss this resist. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.23,1:16:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the level of this experience was\Nabout as low as it gets. Resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.04,1:16:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. And others have to stay there\Nforever.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.60,1:16:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.\NPeople um joke about hell, fool around
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.88,1:16:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to hell. Um and basically people are\Nscared to death of it and um with good
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.44,1:16:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,reason\Nbecause it's worse than your wildest
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.08,1:16:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,imagination of how awful it can be.\NOne's worst imagination is merely the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.15,1:16:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,frosting on the top. From there, it\Nbecomes staggeringly worse.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.15,1:16:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor is there any chance of hope\Nanywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.60,1:17:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it even says on the way down,\Nabandon hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.92,1:17:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That artist\Nwho wrote that, Donnie, I don't know how
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.32,1:17:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he knew that,\Nbut there it is. And it's very very
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.64,1:17:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,visible.\NAbandon all hope. And when you go beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.19,1:17:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessness,\Nthere is a realm unimaginable.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.64,1:17:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet there still remain that chance\Nat that level. And I said, "If there is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.00,1:17:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a God, I ask him to help me.\NThe next experience was a shining forth
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.80,1:17:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of the presence of God as all us\Nin sheer brilliance
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.92,1:18:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,exquisite\Nself-revealing
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.92,1:18:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,wordless silent\Never present.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.92,1:18:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The quality of divinity\Nis stunning.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.64,1:18:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is all that is, includes all that is,\Nand is one's reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.40,1:18:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, beyond time, beyond then or now,\NI think we spoke that now is an illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.96,1:18:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the same as past and future. There is no\Nnow any more than there is a then or a
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.96,1:18:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to be.\NThe reality is an alwaysness
Dialogue: 0,1:18:44.23,1:18:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of forever allness. Allness alwaysness\Nwhich is one's reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.04,1:18:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The celestial realms are more like that\Nmusic. The music takes you really into a
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.44,1:19:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,celestial realm.\NHeavenly is to be in the exquisite state
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.23,1:19:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that that music takes you to\Nand never have to leave it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.71,1:19:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,One can just be in a state of exquisite\Njoy endlessly
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.92,1:19:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because always is always\Nuntil one elects to leave it for some
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.76,1:19:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,reason.\NI don't know what got me off in all
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.67,1:19:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this. This course guitar did that.\NThis card did that. You gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:31.76,1:19:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your fault.\NI don't like talking about such things.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.64,1:19:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are certainly pitfalls and so we\Nwant to be sure and mention them. The
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.08,1:19:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,seduction of the innocent. So the danger\Nof the 500s, the danger of the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.36,1:19:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we've already discussed endless\Nthinkingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.04,1:19:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nconfusing
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.71,1:20:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract concept with reality whereas\Nwhere it's actually only an a concept.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.28,1:20:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the 500s that I've already discussed\Nwith you the downside of the 500s
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.96,1:20:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to get into denial\Nthat all we have to do is be good guys
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.71,1:20:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with Mr. Hitler and he will certainly\Nkeep his agreement with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.84,1:20:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He will not keep his agreement with us.\Nuh that which is not integrous does not
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.44,1:20:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,keep agreements. There's no point in\Nsigning peace treaties with somebody who
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.36,1:20:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 90.\NHe thinks you're an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.44,1:20:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, we suckered him in on that one,\Ndid we?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.32,1:21:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it doesn't mean being a fool. To be\Nspiritual doesn't mean to be a fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.19,1:21:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NHow does one transcend the fear of one's
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.23,1:21:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,own extinction? Yes, that's a good term\Nfor it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:17.19,1:21:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One has to be willing to become extinct\Nto dissolve into nothing
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.12,1:21:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to no longer exist\Nto surrender existence itself that's
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.23,1:21:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,called for but we won't get that to that\Nto the last lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.04,1:21:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anybody getting enlightened\Nbetween now and the last lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.67,1:21:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to be a card carrying member to\Ncross the last doorway.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.60,1:21:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There there is certain confrontations.\NSo each each you see along the way
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.76,1:22:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there's confrontations and trials.\NSpiritual teachings are different. The
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.76,1:22:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,teachers and the teachings are\Ndifferent. And the downside is different
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.88,1:22:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,for each of these levels.\NYou see, if you're over if you're
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.84,1:22:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,overcoming fear, then cowardice is going\Nto take you out, isn't it? This is the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.67,1:22:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,test to see whether or not you can walk\Ninto the bullets and die for your
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.60,1:22:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,country.\NYeah, you're going to walk into them
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.56,1:22:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,bullets and you are going to die.\NThat's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.88,1:22:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you shoot right up here.\NWhen I committed for Harry Kerry, I
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.32,1:22:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,remember the experience was\Nagonizing beyond description. Agonizing.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.36,1:22:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The pain was far worse than what you can\Nimagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.84,1:23:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was horrific.\NAnd with an unstoppable
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.60,1:23:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,will\NI went through it
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.40,1:23:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and came out ecstatic.\Nto be on the body was great.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:15.12,1:23:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The body was agonizing\Nand I was ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.56,1:23:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecstatic.\NNever have to face that one again
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.63,1:23:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to overcome fear. So then the some of\Nthe things that we decry they seem
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.36,1:23:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,we decry Harry Kerry let's say\Nbut it was called for.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.08,1:23:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So I set up a situation in which that\Nwas the only
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.63,1:23:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that could be done and save one's\Nhonor and I did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.80,1:24:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't have to do it again.\NBut there isn't any other way.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.28,1:24:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to actually walk into the\Nbullets and actually die for your
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.44,1:24:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,country. You have to actually rip your\Nguts out and die
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.48,1:24:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for one's faith.\NSo the lessons of spirituality call
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.48,1:24:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,forth then things that seem within the\Nworld quite extreme. We say, "Oh, that's
Dialogue: 0,1:24:25.44,1:24:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,extreme. Look at all the warriors that\Nhad to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.08,1:24:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How are they going to transcend that\Nfear of physical death unless you walk
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.60,1:24:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,right into it?\NYou can't pretend in your mind. Oh, I
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.19,1:24:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,won't be afraid of giving up my body for\NGod. Well, we'll see. Chop.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.15,1:24:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Too late to change your mind now as the\Nsword goes through your skull.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:50.48,1:24:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In a split instant, you realize that\Nyou've just made it. Ecstatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.15,1:25:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you about the time that warrior\Nand myself killed each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.56,1:25:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, we really did it too.\NBoth of us burst into laughter. I killed
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.92,1:25:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,him for Jesus and he killed me for\NAllah. I mean, it was ecstatic. We both
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.36,1:25:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,went out of body and\NGod Jesus amazing. All right. So, you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.63,1:25:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be willing then to take to go to\Nconsiderable extremes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.56,1:25:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your family will think you're mad. They\Nmay call the police, call the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.71,1:25:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,psychiatrist.\NThat was the function I had back east. I
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.40,1:25:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,was a consultant to the Zen monastery,\Nthe Episcopal Dasis, the Catholics
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.36,1:25:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dasis, the nuns,\Nvarious monasteries and religious uh
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.60,1:25:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,retreat centers. This\Nis this guy delusional or is he, you
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.63,1:25:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know, what is his state?\NBecause once you've got that commitment
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.00,1:25:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to God, nothing will stop you. You see,\Ndoctor, he's going to whatchamacallit.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.12,1:26:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, well, yes, let him. But then\Nhe'll die. That's true.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.44,1:26:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The world thinks in very benile terms,\Nboy, he's going to die of that. And I
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.12,1:26:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,said, right.\NAs true he is.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:20.08,1:26:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As true he is.\NIs he in a state of ecstasy or is he
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.71,1:26:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,catatonic?\NIs this a person in high ecstasy or is
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.00,1:26:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this a bipolar manic in the religiosity?\NAnd sometimes it's pretty hard to tell.
